<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="heat-n">heat <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /hiːt/    美 /hiːt/  </p>
<p>[U]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>热；热量：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Ice needs heat to melt.
冰融化需要热量。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>高温；炎热；(烹饪或加热时的) 温度：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>heat wave
酷热期；热浪期</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He adjusted himself very quickly to <strong>the heat</strong> of the country.
他很快适应了这个国家的炎热天气。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Cook food over <strong>a low / medium / high heat</strong>.
用小/中/旺火烹煮食物。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>激烈；激动；激怒：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>in the heat of the argument
在激烈的争论中</p></div>

<h4 id="4-bre-heating">4.★ <strong>暖气 (BrE heating)</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The heat wasn't on, and the house was freezing.
暖气没有开，房子里冰冷。</p></div></div>